Right central venous line is in stable position at the mid SVC, and
 the left PICC line ends near the cavoatrial junction. Gastric tube passes
 below the diaphragm and ends in the body of the stomach. Low lung volumes
 continue to be seen. Previous vascular congestion has improved, and the heart
 size and mediastinal contours are normal. IMPRESSION: No focal consolidation to suggest pneumonia.
